<paragraphs>
    <title>Making New Identities</title>
<p>
    For each of the following, derive a new identity as indicated.
</p>
<ol>
    <li>
        <p workspace="2in">
            Divide the Pythagorean Identity by <m>\cos^2(\theta)</m> to derive a new identity involving <m>\74tan(\theta)</m> and <m>\sec(\theta)</m>.
        </p>
    </li>
    <li>
        <p workspace="3in">
            Use the Pythagorean Identity to create two new versions of the double-angle identity for cosine.
        </p>
    </li>
</ol>

