<page>
<paragraphs>
    <title>Simplifying Trigonometric Expressions</title>
    <p>
        Simplify the following expressions as much as possible.
    </p>
    <ol>
        <li>
            <p workspace="2in">
                <m>\sin(\theta)\tan(\theta) + \cos(\theta)</m>
            </p>
            <hint>
                <p>
                    There should just be one trig function in the end.
                </p>
            </hint>
        </li>
                <li>
        <p workspace="2in">
                <m>\frac{\cos^2(\theta) - 1}{\sin(\theta)}</m>
            </p>
            <hint>
                <p>
                    There should just be one trig function in the end.
                </p>
            </hint>
        </li>
                <li>
            <p workspace="2in">
                <m>\frac{\cos(2\theta)}{\sin(\theta) - \cos(\theta)}</m>
            </p>
            <hint>
                <p>
                    Use the double-angle identity for cosine with both sine and cosine, then factor.
                </p>
            </hint>
        </li>
    
    </ol>
</paragraphs>



